# How to create translated screenshots for the App Store and the Play Store

![][image1]

**Step 1: Open this file \-** [https://www.figma.com/file/loMFSX1wJ61jjuZkSeLV7e/Vignettes-App-Design-(Quentin)?node-id=3248%3A324](https://www.figma.com/file/loMFSX1wJ61jjuZkSeLV7e/Vignettes-App-Design-\(Quentin\)?node-id=3248%3A324)  
**Step 2: If you have edit access, great. Otherwise, request access, or you can make a copy, and notify [Pierre Slamich](mailto:mobile@openfoodfacts.org) when you’re done.** 

* You can spot the source page (Vignettes to be built) and the translated pages generated by the Crowdin plugin

![][image2]  
**Step 3: Ask Pierre to create an automatic translation for your language by commenting, if it does not exist**

**Step 4: Adjust the shapes with text inside since the length might change between English and your language, and the order of words might change too**  
**![][image3]**  
**Step 5: Once you’re done, notify [Pierre Slamich](mailto:mobile@openfoodfacts.org) for final checks and publication**

**Final result for Italian:**  
**![][image4]**
